<h1>Articles listing page</h1>

<table>
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>Title</th>
      <th>Description</th>
      <th colspan="3">Actions</th>
    </tr> 
  </thead>

  <tbody>
    <% @articles.each do |article| %>
      <tr>
        <td><%= article.title %></td>
        <td><%= article.description %></td>
        <td><%= link_to 'Show', article_path(article) %></td>
        <td><%= link_to 'Edit', edit_article_path(article) %></td>
        <td><%= button_to 'Delete', article_path(article), data: { turbo_confirm: "are you sure?"}, method: :delete %></td>
      </tr>
    <% end %>
    <p>If I use link_to routes preference turn to Show, why ??</p>
    <p>If there a bug with turbo gem ?? vid 98</p>
    <p>New degubgger in rails 7?? vid 98</p>
  </tbody>
</table>
<p>
  <%=  link_to 'Create new article', new_article_path %>
</p>